    <thetext>Description of problem:
Firefox is reporting more and more problems like »A coding exception was thrown and uncaught in a Task.« to stdout/stderr. Some applications are forwarding stdout so it will reach syslog, others don&apos;t. So it is not guaranteed that those error messages end up in syslog.

Another issue is with identification: If you click on a link from e.g. evolution which starts firefox, firefox output will be stored in syslog under the evolution.desktop id making it hard to find. To ease debugging and problem reporting it would be useful provide an easier way to find firefox logging output in journald.

Ideally firefox would put its logging output directly into systemd-journald as do most gtk3 applications.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
39.0</thetext>
